<main>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"> / </span>
        <span class="current">Privacy Policy</span>
      </div>
      <span class="legal-eyebrow">🔒 Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="legal-hero-meta">
        <span>📅 Effective Date: March 12, 2026</span>
        <span>🔄 Last Updated: March 12, 2026</span>
        <span>🌍 Applies Globally</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <div class="container">
    <div class="legal-layout">

      <!-- SIDEBAR TOC -->
      <aside class="legal-toc">
        <h6>On This Page</h6>
        <ul class="toc-list">
          <li><a href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
          <li><a href="#data-we-collect">Data We Collect</a></li>
          <li><a href="#how-we-use">How We Use It</a></li>
          <li><a href="#data-sharing">Data Sharing</a></li>
          <li><a href="#cookies">Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#your-rights">Your Rights</a></li>
          <li><a href="#data-retention">Data Retention</a></li>
          <li><a href="#third-party">Third-Party Links</a></li>
          <li><a href="#children">Children's Privacy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#international">International Users</a></li>
          <li><a href="#changes">Policy Changes</a></li>
          <li><a href="#contact">Contact Us</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
      <article class="legal-content">

        <div class="legal-section" id="overview">
          <h2><span class="section-num">01</span> Overview</h2>
          <p>
            Welcome to <strong>Design Tech News</strong> ("we," "us," or "our"), accessible at
            <strong>designtechnews.vercel.app</strong>. We are committed to protecting your personal
            information and your right to privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we
            collect, why we collect it, and how you can update, manage, export, and delete your data.
          </p>
          <p>
            By accessing or using Design Tech News, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
            If you do not agree, please discontinue use of the site.
          </p>
          <div class="legal-highlight">
            <strong>Plain-language summary:</strong> We collect only what we need to run the site and
            newsletter. We do not sell your personal data. You can contact us at any time to access,
            correct, or delete your information.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="data-we-collect">
          <h2><span class="section-num">02</span> Data We Collect</h2>
          <p>We collect information in two ways — information you give us directly and information
          collected automatically when you use the site.</p>

          <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
          <ul class="legal-list">
            <li><strong>Email address</strong> — when you subscribe to our newsletter or contact us.</li>
            <li><strong>Name</strong> — optional, when filling out contact or submission forms.</li>
            <li><strong>Opportunity / job submission details</strong> — if you submit content for listing.</li>
            <li><strong>Messages</strong> — any content you send us via contact forms or email.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
          <ul class="legal-list">
            <li><strong>Usage data</strong> — pages visited, time spent, referring URLs, click patterns.</li>
            <li><strong>Device & browser data</strong> — browser type, operating system, screen resolution.</li>
            <li><strong>IP address</strong> — used for approximate geolocation and spam prevention.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies & similar technologies</strong> — see Section 5 for full details.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We do not collect sensitive personal data such as race, ethnicity, political opinions,
          religious beliefs, health data, or financial information.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="how-we-use">
          <h2><span class="section-num">03</span> How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <p>We use the data we collect for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul class="legal-list">
            <li>To deliver the newsletter and communications you subscribed to.</li>
            <li>To operate, maintain, and improve the website and its content.</li>
            <li>To respond to your enquiries, submissions, or support requests.</li>
            <li>To analyse usage patterns and improve user experience.</li>
            <li>To detect and prevent fraud, spam, and abuse.</li>
            <li>To comply with applicable legal obligations.</li>
            <li>To send you updates about new opportunities, jobs, or news (only if subscribed).</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="legal-highlight">
            We rely on the following legal bases under GDPR: <strong>Consent</strong> (newsletter),
            <strong>Legitimate Interests</strong> (analytics, security), and
            <strong>Legal Obligation</strong> (where required by law). You may withdraw consent at any time.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="data-sharing">
          <h2><span class="section-num">04</span> Data Sharing & Disclosure</h2>
          <p>We do <strong>not sell, rent, or trade</strong> your personal data to third parties.
          We may share your data only in the following limited circumstances:</p>
          <ul class="legal-list">
            <li><strong>Service providers</strong> — trusted vendors who help us operate the site
            (e.g., email delivery via Mailchimp, analytics via Google Analytics). They are
            contractually bound to process data only on our behalf.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal requirements</strong> — if required by law, court order, or governmental
            authority, we may disclose information as necessary.</li>
            <li><strong>Business transfers</strong> — in the event of a merger or acquisition, your
            data may be transferred as part of the transaction. We will notify you in advance.</li>
            <li><strong>With your consent</strong> — for any other purpose, only with your explicit
            prior consent.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="cookies">
          <h2><span class="section-num">05</span> Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
          <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience
          and analyse site traffic. Here's what we use:</p>

          <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
          <p>Required for the site to function correctly (e.g., theme preference — light/dark mode).
          These cannot be disabled.</p>

          <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
          <p>We use <strong>Google Analytics</strong> to understand how visitors interact with the
          site — pages visited, time on site, traffic sources. This data is aggregated and
          anonymised where possible.</p>

          <h3>Marketing / Third-Party Cookies</h3>
          <p>If you click on external job or opportunity links, third-party sites may set their own
          cookies. We have no control over those cookies.</p>

          <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling analytics cookies will
          not affect your ability to use the site. For EU/UK users, we obtain consent for
          non-essential cookies in line with GDPR and the ePrivacy Directive.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="your-rights">
          <h2><span class="section-num">06</span> Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Depending on your location, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>

          <div class="rights-grid">
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">👁️</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Right to Access</strong>
                Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">✏️</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Right to Rectification</strong>
                Correct inaccurate or incomplete information.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">🗑️</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Right to Erasure</strong>
                Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten").
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">🚫</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Right to Object</strong>
                Object to processing of your data for certain purposes.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">📦</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Right to Portability</strong>
                Receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">⏸️</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Right to Restriction</strong>
                Request we limit how we process your data.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">📧</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Withdraw Consent</strong>
                Unsubscribe from emails at any time via the unsubscribe link.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="right-item">
              <span class="right-icon">⚖️</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Right to Complain</strong>
                Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            <strong>California residents (CCPA):</strong> You have the right to know what personal
            information is collected, to opt out of the sale of personal information (we do not sell
            data), and to non-discrimination for exercising your rights.
          </p>
          <p>
            To exercise any right, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:designevangelist1@gmail.com" style="color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;">
              designevangelist1@gmail.com
            </a>. We will respond within 30 days.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="data-retention">
          <h2><span class="section-num">07</span> Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes
          outlined in this policy:</p>
          <ul class="legal-list">
            <li><strong>Newsletter subscribers</strong> — until you unsubscribe, after which your
            email is deleted from our mailing list within 30 days.</li>
            <li><strong>Contact form messages</strong> — retained for up to 12 months, then deleted.</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics data</strong> — anonymised and aggregated; individual session data
            is retained per Google Analytics' retention settings (default 26 months).</li>
            <li><strong>Legal records</strong> — where required by law, we may retain certain data
            for up to 7 years.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="third-party">
          <h2><span class="section-num">08</span> Third-Party Links</h2>
          <p>Design Tech News contains links to external websites, job listings, and opportunity
          pages operated by third parties. Once you leave our site, this Privacy Policy no longer
          applies. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.</p>
          <p>We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of external websites.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="children">
          <h2><span class="section-num">09</span> Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>Design Tech News is not directed at children under the age of 13 (or 16 in the EU/UK).
          We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe we have
          inadvertently collected data from a minor, please contact us immediately at
          <a href="mailto:designevangelist1@gmail.com" style="color:var(--blue);font-weight:600;">
            designevangelist1@gmail.com
          </a> and we will delete it promptly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="international">
          <h2><span class="section-num">10</span> International Users & Data Transfers</h2>
          <p>Design Tech News is operated globally and serves users across Africa, Europe, North
          America, and beyond. Your data may be processed on servers located outside your country
          of residence, including in the United States.</p>
          <p>For users in the European Economic Area (EEA) or United Kingdom, where we transfer
          personal data outside these regions, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place —
          such as Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) — in compliance with GDPR Chapter V.</p>
          <p>By using our site, you consent to the transfer and processing of your data
          as described in this policy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="changes">
          <h2><span class="section-num">11</span> Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our
          practices, technology, or legal requirements. When we make significant changes, we
          will update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page.</p>
          <p>We encourage you to review this policy periodically. Continued use of the site
          after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-section" id="contact">
          <h2><span class="section-num">12</span> Contact Us</h2>
          <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or
          your personal data, please reach out to us:</p>
          <div class="legal-contact-box">
            <h4>Design Tech News — Privacy</h4>
            <p>📧 Email: <a href="mailto:designevangelist1@gmail.com">designevangelist1@gmail.com</a></p>
            <p>🌐 Website: <a href="https://designtechnews.vercel.app">designtechnews.vercel.app</a></p>
            <p style="margin-top:12px;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);">
              We aim to respond to all privacy-related requests within <strong>30 days</strong>.
              For urgent matters, please mark your subject line with "Privacy Request."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>

